2. **Disodium Salt**: 
   - Sodium ions (Na+) are included in the SMILES to neutralize the charge from the phosphate group, indicated as "[Na+].[Na+]".

3. **Combining the Components**: 
   - The cytidine and phosphate components are connected, and the sodium ions are added to neutralize the negative charge of the phosphate group. The stereoisomers and specific connectivity of the ribose and phosphate must be maintained.

Agent3 utilized the ChemDFM tool to derive the SMILES for this molecule, resulting in: "CN(C)c1ccn([C@@H]2O[C@H](COP(=O)([O-])[O-])[C@@H](O)[C@H]2O)c(=O)n1.[Na+].[Na+]".
